name: Skipper Otto at Fishermen's Wharf
address: Skipper Otto at Fishermen's Wharf, 1505 W 1st Ave, Vancouver, BC V6J 1E8

featured_reviews.review_id: Delicious, fresh, local seafood - what more can you ask for! These guys are great. I've picked up at their Fisherman's Wharf location and one of their North Shore spots - both easy and high quality. They have an easy to use online platform, and a great selection.  I never buy seafood anywhere else!

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for this review Anna, and we appreciate your ongoing support as a member! We are so happy to hear you love our wild and sustainable caught Canadian seafood selection!

featured_reviews.review_id:
We have ordered from Skipper Otto for 3 seasons now and absolutely love their products.
We get our orders shipped to Ontario and have never had an issue, we love the quality, freshness, and value. We would definitely recommend Shipper Otto to all fish lovers out there. Keep up the great work guys!
John & Virginia

featured_reviews.review_id:
Great location to buy fresh seafood, especially the spot prawns in May & June!

They are not cheaper compared to the ones at the supermarkets, but you definitely get the freshest seafood of all!

If you live in Vancouver, I recommend this place, why bother go all the way down to Steveston?

featured_reviews.review_id: Excellent initiative. The staff are friendly and will do their best to accommodate requests.  Bought some fresh sustainably caught sockeye salmon and it tasted great!

featured_reviews.review_id: Our family has been members of Skipper Otto for the last few years. The quality of the fish is amazing, it's convenient to order and pick up and the benefit to community and supporting small, local independent fishing families aligns with our values. Thanks for doing what you do!

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Saul for this lovely review. We appreciate your support as a member and so happy to hear you are enjoying the seafood we provide directly from local independent fishing families in Canada.

featured_reviews.review_id: I've been a Skipper Otto's member for over 5 years. Love the ease of ordering online, and so many pickup locations for frozen items. Great selection of seafood too- scallops in the shell, albacore tuna, sablefish, lingcod cheeks, smoked salmon... A picture of the Fisherman who caught your seafood is on the package so you know exactly where it came from and can say a little thanks before eating. Fresh items is a Thursday evening pickup at Fishermans wharf- think spot prawns, mussels or live crab. Great business that I will continue to support.

featured_reviews.review_id: I have ordered online. It's easy! The product is amazing.  The spot prawns are delicious.

featured_reviews.review_id: We have been members of Skipper Otto for several years.  The quality of the products are outstanding. It's easy to order online.  It's easy to do pick-ups at Fisherman's Wharf and at community partners (e.g., Choices).  We believe in the way they do business: supporting local fishing families who catch seafood using sustainable methods.  Every time we've chatted with Skipper Otto staff, we've come away enriched by the conversation and full of admiration for their commitment to our oceans.
